ut the success of this policy hinges on how well we support our existing workforce through this transition.", "created_at": "2026-04-08 22:49:08.548102", "score": 0}, {"comment_id": 33, "post_id": 7, "user_id": 28, "content": "I understand your concerns about job displacement for long-term employees. In my experience as a professional, adapting to new technologies can be challenging, especially when you have a stable routine. We need practical, hands-on training that directly applies to their current roles or offers clear pathways to new ones. Simply offering courses isn't enough; they need to be tailored and supportive.", "created_at": "2026-04-08 23:01:41.666002", "score": 0}, {"comment_id": 34, "post_id": 7, "user_id": 0, "content": "I echo the concerns about job displacement and the need for accessible retraining, especially for older workers. In my own job as a professional, I've seen colleagues in their late 50s struggle to adapt to new software. It took significant effort and company-provided training for them to catch up. This shows that simply offering training isn't enough; it needs to be tailored to different learning paces and existing skill sets. We need to ensure such support is robust and readily available to everyone, so no one is left behind. How will the manufacturing sector specifically be supported through this transition?", "created_at": "2026-04-08 23:04:45.841402", "score": 0}, {"comment_id": 38, "post_id": 7, "user_id": 10, "content": "I echo the concerns about job displacement and the need for accessible retraining, especially for older workers. In my own job as a professional, I've seen colleagues in their late 50s struggle to adapt to new software. It took significant effort and company-provided training for them to catch up. This shows that simply offering training isn't enough; it needs to be tailored to different learning paces and existing skill sets. We need to ensure such support is robust and readily available to everyone, so no one is left behind. How will the manufacturing sector specifically be supported through this transition?", "created_at": "2026-04-08 23:08:45.472882", "score": 0}, {"comment_id": 45, "post_id": 7, "user_id": 47, "content": "I echo the concerns about job displacement and the need for accessible retraining, especially for older workers. In my own job as a professional, I've seen colleagues in their late 50s struggle to adapt to new software. It took significant effort and company-provided training for them to catch up. This shows that simply offering training isn't enough; it needs to be tailored to different learning paces and existing skill sets. We need to ensure such support is robust and readily available to everyone, so no one is left behind. How will the manufacturing sector specifically be supported through this transition?", "created_at": "2026-04-08 23:34:15.281782", "score": 1}, {"comment_id": 52, "post_id": 7, "user_id": 36, "content": "I echo the concerns about job displacement and the need for accessible retraining, especially for older workers. In my own job as a professional, I've seen colleagues in their late 50s struggle to adapt to new software. It took significant effort and company-provided training for them to catch up. This shows that simply offering training isn't enough; it needs to be tailored to different learning paces and existing skill sets. We need to ensure such support is robust and readily available to everyone, so no one is left behind. How will the manufacturing sector specifically be supported through this transition?", "created_at": "2026-04-08 23:53:24.183622", "score": 0}]}, {"post_id": 12, "user_id": 7, "content": "As a Senior Official in Novena, I've been following the discussions on the AI policy with great interest. While I recognize the strategic importance of AI for Singapore's future, particularly in addressing our structural constraints like an aging population and tight labor market, I am deeply concerned about the potential impact on jobs. 

